<exercise id="fs-id1167833142303">
<problem id="fs-id1167833142305">
<para id="fs-id1167836334886">Solve the system of equations <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>{</m:mo><m:mtable><m:mtr><m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:mtd></m:mtr><m:mtr><m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mtd></m:mtr></m:mtable></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓐ</span> by graphing and <span class="token">ⓑ</span> by substitution. <span class="token">ⓒ</span> Which method do you prefer? Why?</para>
